eviously called Gorilla Motor Works<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wolfbrandscooters.com/|title=49cc 50cc 150cc Gas Powered Motor Scooters / Mopeds &#124; Wholesale Scooter & Moped Distributor|website=Wolf Brand Scooters}}</ref>\n|-\n| Xingyue || China ||\n|-\n| [[Yamaha Motor Corporation|Yamaha]] || Japan|| [[Yamaha Corporation]]\n|-\n| Yiying || China || Manufactured by Benzhou Vehicle Industry Group Co., Ltd. and Taizhou Huangyan Yiying Motorcycle Co., Ltd.<ref>http://auto-che.com/m/taizhou-huangyan-yiying-motorcycle-co-ltd/scooter.html</ref> \n|-\n| Zhongyu || China || Jiangmen Zhongyu Motor (Group) Co., Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.made-in-china.com/showroom/alanmotor|title=China motorcycle manufacturer, engine, scooter supplier - Jiangmen Zhongyu Motor (Group) Co., Ltd.|website=www.made-in-china.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Zongshen]] || China || [[Zongshen|Chongqing Zongshen Power Machinery Company]]; has a relationship with [[Piaggio]] through Zongshen Piaggio Foshan Motorcycle Co.,Ltd<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cccme.org.cn/shop/cccme11393/index.aspx|title=ZONGSHEN PIAGGIO FOSHAN MOTORCYCLE CO.,LTD.|website=www.cccme.org.cn}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Znen]] || China || Zhongneng Vehicle Group Co., Ltd.; petrol and electric scooters. Sold under numerous brands including Jinlun (worldwide), Lexmoto (UK), Tamoretti (UK, Netherlands), Dorton (Spain), Mondial (Turkey), and in the USA Paparazzi's, Flyscooters, Lance, and BMS. Owners of Moto Morini. \n|-\n| Zunlong || China || Manufactured by Benzhou Vehicle Industry Group Co., Ltd. and Taizhou Huangyan Yiying Motorcycle Co., Ltd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://auto-che.com/b/zunlong.html|title=Zunlong Made In China|website=auto-che.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Z Electric Vehicle]] || USA || All electric range\n|}\n\n==Scooter brands and manufacturers no longer in scooter production==\n*Accumolli (1950), [[Piaggio]] powered  &mdash; Italy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.woiweb.com/wiki/index.php?title=Accumolli|title=Accumolli - WOI Encyclo