r sold Lifan based scooters until at least 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autosoviet.altervista.org/ENGLISH-automotorusse9moto(Voskhod).htm|title=Autosoviet: VOSKHOD|website=www.autosoviet.altervista.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zid.ru/products/civil/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019052900/http://zid.ru/products/civil/|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 19, 2018|title=\u0417\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434 \u0438\u043c. \u0412.\u0410. \u0414\u0435\u0433\u0442\u044f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0430 / \u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0446\u0438\u044f|date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> &mdash; Russia \n*[[Z\u00fcndapp]] (1953\u20141964) &mdash; West Germany\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of motorcycle manufacturers]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Companies by industry}}\n\n[[Category:Motor scooters| ]]\n[[Category:Scooter manufacturers| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of manufacturers|Scooter manufacturers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nNote there is no single fixed definition of a '''[[Scooter (motorcycle)|scooter]]''' (also known by the full name '''motor-scooter'''), but generally a smaller motorcycle with a [[step-through frame]] is considered a scooter, especially if it has a floor for the rider's feet (as opposed to straddling the vehicle like a conventional motorcycle). Other common traits of scooters can include: bodywork (so the mechanicals are not exposed like a conventional motorcycle), motors combined with the suspension or wheel (rather than attached to the frame like a conventional motorcycle), leg shields, smaller wheels than a conventional motorcycle, and an alternative to a chain drive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scooterfocus.com/what_is_a_scooter.html|title=What is a Scooter, Moped or Motorcycle?|website=www.scooterfocus.com}}</ref> \n\nScooters share traits with [[moped]]s, and some models could even be considered both a moped and a scooter. Adding to the confusion in many areas most scooters are road registered in the same category originally designed for mopeds (and usually still called \"moped\" class), leading to scooters being referred to as \"mopeds\" in such areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.carolenash.com/insidebikes/news/scooter-moped-motorcycle/|title=What is a Scooter, Moped or Motorcycle?|date=August 20, 2015|website=Carole Nash}}</ref> [[Underbone |Underbones]] also share traits with scooters, but are generally not considered scooters as they do not have a floor. \n\n==Scooter brands in production==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Manufacturer / brand !! Nationality !! Group / notes\n\n|-[[Adiva]] || Italy/Taiwan || ADIVA S.r.l. - Advanced Vehicles; uses various engines from 150 -400).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adiva.it/ita/index.html}}</ref> Largely Taiwanese built range. \n|-\n| [[Adly]] || Taiwan ||  Her Chee Industrial Co Ltd; previously US market brands included AMS, Jui Li, and Grycner (using German supplied Sachs 505 engines). Currently Taiwanese built range. \n|-\n| [[Aeon (motors)|Aeon]] || Taiwan || Aeon Motor\n|-\n| [[AJS]] || United Kingdom || Manufactured in China (from 2002)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ajsmotorcycles.co.uk/scooters|title=AJS Motorcycles Ltd. &#124; 125cc & 50cc Scooters|website=ajs-motorcycles-ltd}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chinesemotorcyclepartsonline.co.uk/manufacturers/AJS|title=AJS Parts &#124; CMPO &#124; Chinese Motorcycle Parts Online|website=www.chinesemotorcyclepartsonline.co.uk}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Aprilia]] || Italy|| [[Piaggio|Piaggio & C. SpA.]]\n|-\n| Askoll || Italy|| Askoll Group; all electric range \n|-\n|[[Avangan]]\n|Iran\n|Manufacturer of [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|electric scooters]]\n|-\n| [[Bajaj Auto|Bajaj]] ||India|| [[Bajaj Auto|Bajaj Auto Ltd]]; 1960s licensed Vespa models, from 1971 unlicensed Vespa-like scooters\n|-\n| [[Baotian Motorcycle Company|Baotian]] || China || Baotian Motorcycle Industrial C